#X text 18 69 The frequency modulation procedure is simple and we have already sone some simple low frequency modulation in earlier examples. We just need to add the carrier signal (aka carrier frequency) to the modulating signal. Revisiting an older example on additive synthesis we have a frequency of 500hz being randomly modulated by low frequency noise in 12 channels. One could have a single frequency/channel being modulated by a LFO for a simple vibrato effect., f 65;
#X text 73 581 Before getting into proper FM synthesis \, let's expand on the idea of simple/slower pitch modulation. for instance \, we can expand on the earlier subtractive synthesis example and add an envelope modulation to the pitch \, in this case a simple decay envelope that goes from a 3 to 1 ratio in one second. Hence \, dropping from an octave plus a fifth to the original pitch. You can think of more complex situations like a decay and a release envelope as an excercize. Ok \, now we can get into the real business of Frequency Modulation in the next example., f 84;
